The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 17 November is 103,084 (11,881 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 12 November, there were 4,473 new confirmed cases (515.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 05 November, there were 3,993 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 12% (480 extra cases).
